7 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
8 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
9 Article – Transportation
10 SUBTITLE 13. MARYLAND AREA RAIL COMMUTER (MARC) RAIL AUTHORITY.
11 7–1301.
12 (A) IN THIS SUBTITLE THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
13 INDICATED.
14 (B) “MARC” MEANS MARYLAND AREA RAIL COMMUTER RAIL SERVICE.
15 (C) “MARC RAILROAD FACILITIES PROJECT” INCLUDES:
16 (1) (I) THE BRUNSWICK, CAMDEN, OR PENN LINES OF THE
17 MARYLAND AREA RAIL COMMUTER (MARC) SERVICE; AND
18 (II) EXTENDING MARC SERVICE; AND
19 (2) ANY ADDITIONS, IMPROVEMENTS, OR ENLARGEMENTS TO ANY OF
20 THE PROJECTS LISTED UNDER ITEM (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION, WHENEVER
21 AUTHORIZED.
22 7–1302.
23 THERE IS A MARC RAIL AUTHORITY.
24 7–1303.
25 (A) (1) THE SECRETARY IS THE CHAIR OF THE MARC RAIL AUTHORITY.
26 (2) THE SECRETARY SHALL DESIGNATE AN EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR
27 OF THE MARC RAIL AUTHORITY.
28 (B) IN ADDITION TO THE CHAIR, THE MARC RAIL AUTHORITY CONSISTS OF
29 THE FOLLOWING MEMBERS:

HOUSE BILL 517 3
1 (1) (I) ONE MEMBER WITH A BACKGROUND IN RAIL TRANSIT,
2 APPOINTED BY THE PRESIDENT OF THE SENATE; AND
3 (II) ONE MEMBER WITH A BACKGROUND IN RAIL TRANSIT,
4 APPOINTED BY THE SPEAKER OF THE HOUSE; AND
5 (2) AS AN EX OFFICIO MEMBER, THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR OF THE
6 MARC RAIL AUTHORITY.
7 (C) (1) THE TERM OF AN APPOINTED MEMBER IS 4 YEARS.
8 (2) AN APPOINTED MEMBER MAY NOT SERVE MORE THAN THREE
9 CONSECUTIVE TERMS.
10 (3) AT THE END OF A TERM, A MEMBER CONTINUES TO SERVE UNTIL
11 A SUCCESSOR IS APPOINTED AND QUALIFIES.
12 (4) A MEMBER WHO IS APPOINTED AFTER A TERM HAS BEGUN SERVES
13 ONLY FOR THE REST OF THE TERM AND UNTIL A SUCCESSOR IS APPOINTED AND
14 QUALIFIES.
15 (D) AN APPOINTED MEMBER OF THE MARC RAIL AUTHORITY IS ENTITLED
16 TO:
17 (1) THE COMPENSATION PROVIDED IN THE STATE BUDGET; AND
18 (2) REIMBURSEMENT FOR EXPENSES UNDER THE STANDARD STATE
19 TRAVEL REGULATIONS, AS PROVIDED IN THE STATE BUDGET.
20 (E) THE MARC RAIL AUTHORITY IS SUBJECT TO THE OPEN MEETINGS
21 ACT UNDER TITLE 3 OF THE GENERAL PROVISIONS ARTICLE.
22 7–1304.
23 (A) THE MARC RAIL AUTHORITY IS ENTITLED TO THE STAFF PROVIDED IN
24 THE STATE BUDGET.
25 (B) THE SECRETARY SHALL PROVIDE THE MARC RAIL AUTHORITY WITH
26 THE PERSONNEL OF THE DEPARTMENT THAT THE SECRETARY CONSIDERS
27 NECESSARY FOR PERFORMANCE OF THE MAINTENANCE AND OTHER FUNCTIONS
28 REQUIRED OF THE MARC RAIL AUTHORITY TO MEET ITS OBLIGATIONS WITH
29 RESPECT TO ITS MARC RAILROAD FACILITIES PROJECTS.

