1 7–1305.
2 (A) (1) ACTING ON BEHALF OF THE DEPARTMENT, THE MARC RAIL
3 AUTHORITY HAS THOSE POWERS AND DUTIES RELATING TO THE SUPERVISION,
4 FINANCING, CONSTRUCTION, OPERATION, MAINTENANCE, AND REPAIR OF MARC
5 RAILROAD FACILITIES PROJECTS AS ARE GRANTED TO IT BY THIS SUBTITLE.
6 (2) THE MARC RAIL AUTHORITY MAY:
7 (I) DELEGATE PROJECT OPERATIONS, MAINTENANCE, AND
8 REPAIR TO THE ADMINISTRATION; AND
9 (II) USE FARE REVENUE TO PROVIDE THE ADMINISTRATION
10 WITH PAYMENTS FOR PROJECT OPERATIONS, MAINTENANCE, AND REPAIR.
11 (B) THE MARC RAIL AUTHORITY HAS GENERAL SUPERVISION OF MARC
12 RAILROAD FACILITIES PROJECTS.
13 (C) THE MARC RAIL AUTHORITY SHALL FINANCE, CONSTRUCT, OPERATE,
14 REPAIR, AND MAINTAIN IN GOOD ORDER THE MARC RAILROAD FACILITIES.
15 (D) THE MARC RAIL AUTHORITY SHALL, TO THE EXTENT PRACTICABLE,
16 ADHERE TO THE TRANSIT PLANS PREPARED UNDER SUBTITLE 3 OF THIS TITLE.
17 7–1306.
18 (A) THE MARC RAIL AUTHORITY MAY ACQUIRE, HOLD, AND DISPOSE OF
19 PROPERTY IN THE EXERCISE OF ITS POWERS AND PERFORMANCE OF ITS DUTIES.
20 (B) THE MARC RAIL AUTHORITY MAY MAKE ANY CONTRACTS AND
21 AGREEMENTS NECESSARY OR INCIDENTAL TO THE EXERCISE OF ITS POWERS AND
22 PERFORMANCE OF ITS DUTIES.
23 (C) THE MARC RAIL AUTHORITY MAY APPLY FOR AND RECEIVE GRANTS
24 FROM ANY FEDERAL AGENCY FOR THE PLANNING, CONSTRUCTION, OPERATION, OR
25 FINANCING OF ANY PASSENGER RAIL OR TRANSIT PROJECT AND MAY RECEIVE AID
26 OR CONTRIBUTIONS OF MONEY, PROPERTY, LABOR, OR OTHER THINGS OF VALUE
27 FROM ANY SOURCE, TO BE HELD, USED, AND APPLIED FOR THE PURPOSES FOR
28 WHICH THE GRANTS, AID, AND CONTRIBUTIONS ARE MADE.
29 (D) THE MARC RAIL AUTHORITY MAY ADOPT RULES AND REGULATIONS TO
30 CARRY OUT THE PROVISIONS OF THIS SUBTITLE.

